Observation Made so far from EDA Analysis

  1. It made sense that the if you have more credit card, the customer would make less visits to the bank. Hence the negative correlation.
  2. If a customer tends to have more credit cards then their credit card limit will naturally be high since they have the ability to pay out each credit card limit.
  3. The customer will visit online banking portals more often because if they have more credit cards most of the transaction and maintenance will be done through the online format.
  4. There seems to be too many outliers in the Avg_Credit_limit. It seems to be left skewed so that columns need so to be adjusted or scaled or the outliers need to be eliminated.

In the below block of code we are searching for the best cluster pattern to find out the types of groups of customers in the dataset.

In [292]:
#In the below block of code we are searching for the best cluster pattern to find out the types of groups of customers in the dataset.
#where considered 15 clusters
cluster_range = range(1,15)
cluster_errors = []
for num_clusters in cluster_range:
    clusters = KMeans(num_clusters, n_init = 10)
    clusters.fit(credit_costumer)
    labels = clusters.labels_
    centroids = clusters.cluster_centers_
    cluster_errors.append(clusters.inertia_)

clusters_df = pd.DataFrame({"num_clusters": cluster_range, "cluster_errors": cluster_errors})
clusters_df[0:15]

# The best value is 1 and the worst value is -1. 
#Values near 0 indicate overlapping clusters. 
#Negative values generally indicate that a sample has been assigned to the wrong cluster, as a different cluster is more similar.
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_samples, silhouette_score
predictions = kmeans.predict(credit_costumer_3)
predictions
#S1 =  {silhouette_score(credit_costumer_3, predictions)}
S1a = silhouette_score(credit_costumer_3, predictions)
print(S1a)
print(f'Silhouette Score(n=3: {S1a}')
credit_costumer_3["group"] = predictions
credit_costumer_3['group'] = credit_costumer_3['group'].astype('category')

Group 0: They are the customers with the average credit limit, holding minimum number of credit cards but they attempt to call a bank rarely but prefer to do transction in person than in online.

Group 1: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, not having credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and they do not perfered to do transaction by in person and sometimes in online.

Group 2(Premium): They are the customers with the high credit limit, holding many number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and rarely visits the bank in person but they perfered to do transaction in online most of the time.

Group 0: They are the customers with the average credit limit, holding minimum number of credit cards but they attempt to call a bank rarely but prefer to do transction in person than in online.

Group 1: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, not holding credit cards but they attempt to call a bank more frequently but rarely visits the bank in person or in online.

Group 2: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, holding above average number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and they do not perfered to do transaction by in person and online.

Group 3: They are the customers with the high credit limit, holding many number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and rarely visits the bank in person but they perfered to do transaction in online most of the time.

Conclusion:

  1. As per the elbow method number of clusters to be opted for K means is 3 and slight deviation is there at four as well. so k means and hierarchical cluster algorithms, both are formed with 3 and 4 clusters and tested for the given problem.
  2. Observed that k- means algorithm with 3 clusters has given silhoutte score as .49 where in for 4 number of clusters the silhoutte score as .38
  3. silhoutte score is always beween -1 to 1 for better clustering it would be 1 and - means bad clustering the best value is 1 and the worst value is -1. Values near 0 indicate overlapping clusters. Negative values generally indicate that a sample has been assigned to the wrong cluster, as a different cluster is more similar. Here, silhoutte score is .49 for k-means clustering algorithm with 3 number of clusters than with the 4 clusters.
  4. Similarly silhoutte score and cophenetic score is computed for the hierarchical clustering with 3 and 4 cluster with the distance computation using Euclidean method and Average, complete and ward linkage methods.

  5. Amongst all the three linkage methods 'complete' linkage with the three clusters has given the best silhoutte score as .56 which is closer to 1 but cophentic score is not so good as in average linkage method with 3 number of clusters.

  6. As a conclusion hierarchical clustering with 'Average linkage' with the three clusters has given better results on cophenetic score and a ery meager is present in the silhoutte score. cophenet index is a measure of the correlation between the distance of points in feature space and distance on dendrogram closer it is to 1, the better is the clustering. so hierarchical clustering with average linkage with the three clusters is the best unsupervised algorithm for the given problem. ( The reasons being very good cophenetic score and at par level of silhoutte )

Group 0: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, not holding credit cards but they attempt to call a bank more frequently but rarely visits the bank in person or in online.

Group 1: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, holding minimum number of credit cards but they attempt to call a bank rarely but prefer to do transction in person than in online.

Group 2: They are the customers with the high credit limit, holding many number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and rarely visits the bank in person but they perfered to do transaction in online most of the time.

Group 3: They are the customers with the high credit limit, holding many number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and they perfered to do transaction by in person but they are not perfered to do transaction in online.

1.How many different segments of customers are there?

There are three groups of customers. But 4 groups of customers could also be a possibility. But the results have been concluded for both the different set of groups

2. How are these segments different from each other?

As per K-means:

Group 0: They are the customers with the average credit limit, holding minimum number of credit cards but they attempt to call a bank rarely but prefer to do transction in person than in online.

Group 1: They are the customers with the below minimum credit limit, not having credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and they do not perfered to do transaction by in person and sometimes in online.

Group 2(Premium): They are the customers with the high credit limit, holding many number of credit cards. They do not attempt to call a bank and rarely visits the bank in person but they perfered to do transaction in online most of the time.

As per Hierarchial Clustering:

Group 0: They are the customers with the below average credit limit, holding minimum number of credit cards but they attempt to call the bank very frequently and prefer to do transaction online.

Group 1 (Premium): They are the customers with the very good minimum credit limit and have many credit cards. They prefer to do transactions online.

Group 2:: They are the customers with the average credit limit and do not hold many number of credit cards. They prefer to bank transactions in person.

What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

Since Hierarchial clustering is better the suggestions have been made for HC average linkage which seemed to show better results. ( As per Cophenetic and Silhouette Score

Recommendation for 3 Groups:

For Group 0 : These are the customers who have low credit limit. For this group the bank should provide financial education to help the customer improve their credibility and manage finances. This will help the group gain a better credit score which in turn increases their credit-limit with the bank. This group of customers can be targeted for getting more credit cards and hence improve bank business. Since they frequently call the bank there is a high possibilty they are in need of credit cards.

For Group 1: For the customers in this group the bank should try and improve their online banking experience and ensure they have a smooth experience through better User Interface services eg: More interactive and user friendly experience, better online security etc.

For Group 2 : These are the customers who prefer to come to the bank for their banking transactions. For this group the bank should try to improve in-house facilities and provide better hospitality. The bank should also encourage these customers to try the online banking services.

Recommendation for 4 Groups:

For group 2 ( Premium Customer ) : For the customers in this group the bank should try and improve their online banking experience and ensure they have a smooth experience through better User Interface services eg: More interactive and user friendly experience, better online security etc.

For group 3 ( Premium Customer) : These are the customers who prefer to come to the bank for their banking transactions. For this group the bank should try to improve in-house facilities and provide better hospitality. The bank should also encourage these customers to try the online banking services.

For group 1 ( Non- Premium Customer) : These are the customers who have low credit limit. For this group the bank should provide financial education to help the customer improve their credibility and manage finances. This will help the group gain a better credit score which in turn increases their credit-limit with the bank. This group of customers can be targeted for getting more credit cards and hence improve bank business. Since they frequently call the bank there is a high possibilty they are in need of credit cards.

For group 0 ( Non- Premium Customer ): These are the customers who have low credit limit. For this group the bank should provide financial education to help the customer improve their credibility and manage finances.

Difference between Hierarchial and K-means

From the K-means and Heirarchical clustering, Group 3 seem to hold similar properties. But Group 1 and 2 seem to differ in the credit limit and total credits cards. In Group 0 for K-mean it shows average credit limit but in HC it shows below minimum credit limit.
